messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hello, there has been a murder-suicide. There are no survivors. Please send help.
What's the address of your emergency?
My ex-boyfriend broke into my house and killed my current boyfriend and then killed himself.
Okay, did you just find them?
No, he killed my current boyfriend and then he held me hostage and just shot himself in the head.
Just now?
Yeah.
Okay, stay on the line with me. Did he hurt you?
He kind of beat me up, and my parents aren't home. It's just me, and I'm 17.
What's his name?
Brian White and Jake Burns are the victims.
Burns, B-U-R-N-S?
Yes.
Where are the weapons right now?
The axe is in Jake's head and the gun is in Brian's hand.
Where are you inside the house?
I'm sitting in our breakfast nook. Brian's in the living room. There's the kitchen between us.
Okay. Don't touch anything, okay? Can you do me a favor? Can you go sit on the porch?
Yes.
What's your name?
Desiree Staper.
Are you okay to walk?
I can't walk. He beat me up.
Okay, just stay there. Are you still tied up?
No.
Do you need an ambulance?
Yes.
Okay, what happened?
I put too much pressure on my leg.
How long did he hold you captive?
Since about eight o'clock this morning.
Did he break into the house?
Yeah, he watched my mom leave and came in while Jake and I were sleeping.
Okay, are you on the porch right now?
Yes, but my leg really hurts.
Okay, do you need an ambulance?
I need a medic, yes, but I don't need to go to the hospital.
Okay, we have help on the way. Just stay on the line with me.
I just want to get these bodies out of my house.
Okay, we'll take care of that. Is there anyone else in the house?
No.
Where does Brian live?
I don't know his address, but he lives on Houghton.
Okay, do you know his middle name and date of birth?
His middle name is Douglas. He would be 20 tomorrow.
The officer should be approaching you right now. Stay on the line with me until you're with the officer, okay?
Yes, he's coming up right now.
Okay, go ahead and talk to the officer, Desiree.
Thank you.
You're welcome. Bye-bye.
